A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Bethann Frillman; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Bethann Frillman has achieved success as a vice president of a Fortune 100
3 international division, a Georgia small business owner, and an engaged community leader,
4 wielding expertise in strategic planning, risk analysis, and program management; and
5 WHEREAS, she has dedicated more than two decades to the Atlanta community, where she
6 has played a key role in voter protection efforts and the improvement of the DeKalb County
7 election process; and
8 WHEREAS, as a volunteer and DeKalb County liaison for voter protection efforts, she
9 supported the DeKalb County Ad Hoc Elections Committee, developed and maintained
10 precinct-level voting statistics to support Get Out the Vote initiatives, and analyzed the
11 elections budget to keep county officials informed; and
12 WHEREAS, she has further contributed to the Voter Protection Hotline by assisting voters,
13 communicating with county election officials, and leading a team that analyzed more than
14 9,000 hotline call records to strengthen state and county voter protection efforts; and
