15 WHEREAS, as the founder and owner of Bethann Frillman Photography, she successfully
16 managed all aspects of her fine art portrait and commercial photography business, including
17 business development, marketing, operations, and finance; and
18 WHEREAS, she has additionally held executive leadership roles in the airline industry,
19 serving as Vice President of Pacific Marketing for Continental Airlines, where she managed
20 $1 billion in Asia-Pacific revenue, oversaw 100 staff members across 12 countries, and
21 successfully launched the airline's first United States to Japan service; and
22 WHEREAS, she was Chief of Staff for Senator Elena Parent for two years, and in that
23 capacity, she made it more seamless and efficient for Georgia's high school students to
24 achieve lifetime success through dual enrollment; and
25 WHEREAS, she and her husband, Subodh, share two successful adult sons; and
26 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentlewoman has given inspiration to many through her high
27 ideals, morals, and deep concern for her fellow citizens, and she possesses the vast wisdom
28 which only comes through experience and the strength of character which is achieved
29 through overcoming the many challenges of life; and
30 WHEREAS, Bethann Frillman is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable
31 reputation for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
32 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
33 remarkable and distinguished individual be appropriately recognized.
